name: Between The Sun and Moon
description:
A collaboration between omentejovem and Jesperish, standing between the sun and the moon. We live on opposite sides of the Earth, looking at the same sun and moon. Realizing we share the same universe, we express our desire for freedom and belonging. We connected through the internet and met up in Portugal to turn our digital artwork into a physical print, placing our creation between the sun and the moon, as part of our cycle.

Printed on a Hahnemühle Photo Rag 308g - 108,23 x 100cm  
Signed in the back by both artists

name: Out of Babylon
description:
Personally, this artwork symbolizes change for me. I have made the difficult decision to move back to the countryside, to be closer to old friends and family. I also see that this art resonates with my previous piece, 'Cheap Problems.' It has been a challenging change and decision, and I'm still in the process. I used to believe that the big city was synonymous with success and well-being, but the urban environment comes with various issues and situations that I prefer to deal with occasionally, perhaps during a trip or something similar.

I imagine I will feel better in my hometown where I grew up, surrounded by friends who have been with me since before my journey as 'omentejovem,' and of course, my family. And if I don't feel better, things are not set in stone, and I will be able to make another decision if I choose to. I believe this change will allow me to travel more and meet other friends along the way. I feel the need for a home and a place where I feel good, with people who make me feel good, with love and less rush and selfishness from the big city.

description: "Ether-Man ll" is a continuation from my first ever edition on Ethereum Blockchain called "Ether-Man", which firstly was minted on 01/11/2021 through the OpenSea Shared contract but has the ability to burn and get it on my own contract. The artwork speaks about my gratitude and needing from my collectors support and faith to keep achieving good things with my creative passion and crafts on my career. I believe an artist can't build a legacy alone, without relationships, and with both of our forces and faith, good things can come. I believe we all can't be really independent from relationships and nature, it would be non-natural if so. A big thank you for all my collectors, I'm happy that is my first ever mint on 2024. Let's go!

name: Before Cycles Could Turn in Stories
description:
Telling a story about my life, or the past one. When I realized that I could express myself with digital art, not only for design commissions. When I prayed every day to make the right decisions. When my cat was the only company I had while working all night. When dreams seemed distant, but also very close. When I couldn't buy gifts for my girl...

I am deeply honored to be able to present this work on SuperRare Opening Gallery, the first platform that believed in my work and desire to create digital artworks, where I got my first collectors and believers. The day I got accepted on SuperRare late 2020 was the day I realized I can make much more happen with my artwork, I told all my friends how optimistic I was and they understand why months later. I still see myself a lot on this artwork, in the present, I still feel that I am stuck on some life cycles and maybe after many years I might feel the same. I'm just happy to be heard and seen, to be able to tell my stories or by others. I'm just happy to be able to do artworks from Brazil and access the world with it, the blockchain gave me the chance and I felt the need to stop everything and dedicate my life to leaving my mark on it.

"Before Cycles Could Turn in Stories" portrays my desire to express, to let my craft be my life. A 1 of 1 artwork that precedes a series of 10 artworks that I have been working on and conceptualizing for almost two years, called "Stories on Circles". Thank you for listening, I think we can all learn from others and understand their perspective. Stories are visions that we share together, that fortunately we have particularities. Stories that happened to me, might happen to you, and surely are happening with someone right now.

name: Cheap Problems
description:
Recently, I went through a phase where I questioned why I was giving so much attention to certain problems in my life, especially after my dad's heart surgery. I realized that I want to focus on love and being the best version of myself, not just for my own benefit, but also for others. This inspired me to create the artwork called "Cheap Problems."

I created most of the piece while traveling back home in the bus to see my dad in the hospital after I knew about his heart attack. The artwork serves as a reminder to prioritize love and not waste energy on insignificant issues. The name comes from a past chat I had with my friend and fellow artist, Aleqth.

I am excited to continue experimenting and pursuing my passion while prioritizing my happiness, health, and relationships. "Cheap Problems" has become a personal mantra, a way to stay grounded and focused on what truly matters in life.

name: Sun & Moon
description: "Sun & Moon" is a continuation of the artwork "Peixe-Dourado no AZuL". When I was finishing AZuL, which uses Tjo's CC0 piece "BLeU", I felt a desire to just add yellow paint to the work, leaving only the Sun and the Moon visible. I needed to mint it somehow, be it as editions or as a 1 of 1. I decided to make it the bidder's editions for AZuL, however it became a 1 of 1 after @kutoacapital made the only and highest bid in the auction.
